description:
Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.1.
Rectangular shaft, leading at once on north through a round topped door into a barrel vaulted chamber.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.3.
Rect. shaft, chamber to south. N-S.
In shaft, well below burial A. (over)
(a) Nine vases of refined clay [drawings]
(b) Three pieces coral
(c) Alab. mortar & 2 pestles
(d) Two bl. gl. scarabs (over)
(e) Bronze hook & tweezers
(f) Gold earring.
(g) Bl. gl. & glass & shell beads ([shaft & chamber]
(h) 4 bl. gl. amulets
(i) 2 black amulets [chamber]
(j) Small alab. vase & lid [drawing]

Scarabs [drawings]
Burial A. in coffin high in shaft, head S.
In S. chamber several burials.
(a) A child with 7 bl. gl. amulets at neck
(b) Bronze vase
(c) Small buff clay vase wheel made
(d) Large pear shaped bead of rock crystal.
(e) Red pottery bowl [drawing]

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.4.
Rect. shaft, N & S, chamber S.
In chamber child in coffin, on l. side head north.
(a) Two small ivory vases (?)
(b) Bl. gl. scarab, no inscription.
(c) Mother of pearl discs.
(d) Two shells & cowry
(e) Bead [drawing]
(f) Bl. beads & amulets.
(g) 2 vases (one prob. intrusive) [drawings]
[Large vase with lines of v. young body. prob. from next shaft (broken) Large vase with inscription.]

Tomb: T.5, 6, 17
T.5.
Body hunched up at lower end of coffin in turba. Head N, feet S.
T.6.
Body head W, legs E in turba across top of T.4.
T.17. Long shaft. At top boy's body in coffin supine, head to S. on left side
Chamber to S. Disturbed, one body in sandaq, mirror at head [(?) N] end 
Two vases [drawings] apparently late.
Beads [drawing] black & white

Tomb: T.8.
T.8. Turba N & S. Body supine in wood coffin head to S.
(a) Mother of pearl beads
(b) Bl. gl. beads
(c) White discoid beads.
(d) Fragments of leather.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.11. & 12, 13, 14
T.11 & 12
Two rectangular coffins under a late wall.Both N.W-S.E & side by side, feet to N.W.
No furniture.
T.13.
Body in sarcoph. with stucco & paint lid. Coffin shaped at shoulders. Supine, head to west. No furniture
T.14. Turba, body broken up, under wall masses of long bl. gl. beads.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.21.
VI. Dyn. shaft. Chamber to west but only slightly undercut. Body disturbed in wooden coffin. Head to N.W. No furniture.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.22.
VI. Dyn shaft. Chamber to north but only slightly undercut. Body in wooden coffin, plundered & disturbed.
(a) thick alab vase [drawing]
(b) Bone seal [drawing]
(c) Bone pendant [drawing]
[(d) Bead of dark & light bl. gl.] [drawing]
VI. Dyn pot in radim above [drawing]

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.25, 26, 27, 28
T.25.
VI. Dyn. square shaft, body only. No furniture, chamber west, slightly undercut only, head N., body on r. side.
T.26.
VI. Dyn square shaft. Chamber east, body on left side, head north, female. no furniture, thick wooden coffin
T.27.
VI. Dyn. Suqare shaft. Two coffins bodies on l.side. No furniture. [plan]
T.28.
VI. Dyn shaft (?) Body disturbed, no finds. [plan]

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.31, 32, 33.
T.31. See over.
T.32. Child's body beside wall of T.31. Plundered. 8 cowries, 5 bl. gl. amulets & 4 bl. gl. beads.
T.33. Small vaulted chamber. N. of T.31. Long bl. gl. beads. 4 jackal figs. & winged beetle in bad green glaze.

T.41
Trench burial, badly upset. Head & legs only, one bl. gl. scarab. (drawing of scarab with inscription)

T.42
Turba N  S. Head north, supine.

T.43
Turba, E & W, feet west. Head rest sideways under head, supine. Discoid beads  & mother of pearl. Bl. gl. beads, shells, part of bl. gl. Bez figure.

T.44
Turba, boy in coffin, head N, on left side.
Pottery 52 XVII     ,Potery 54 VI dyn.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.57, 58.
T.57.
Disturbed turba.
small shell beads & large gold bead.
T.58. Rect shaft N-S. Chamber to S
man's body badly damaged.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.61, 62, 63
61.
VI Dyn shaft
62. VI Dyn shaft. Coffin of mud [plan]
mud coffin, no skeleton
63. VI Dyn shaft, ch to east
parts of female body, yellow hair, head to N. No finds

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.64, 65
T.64. Rect. shaft. Mummy near top, male, head S. N&S
Lower a large wooden coffin, woman on right side, head to N
Wooden rabbit, shells
Bl. gl. amulets [drawing]
Glaze beads [drawing]
2 stone beads
T.65 VI Dyn square, chamber to W.
man, left side, head N.
One pot at waist
Both arms broken & badly joined
red ware [drawing]

[drawing]
130 long x 70 broad

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.67., 68
67
Rect. shaft, chamber to north, made entirely of finely cut limestone with door of same.
Wooden sarcoph. in shaft, broken & taken from chamber
In shaft 11 miniature vases [drawings]
68 Ridged shaft v. narrow, chambers never finished, north & south.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.69, 70
69. Ridged shaft v. narrow.
70. Ridged rect. shaft, body in shaft badly disturbed.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.71.
T.71.
Rect. shaft, ridged below the bricks, N & S [drawing]
Two chambers S, narrow.
Upper empty exe. for bones.
Lower chamber, bones disturbed
(a) Fragts. of 2 painted coffins 
man (?) & child, hands
(b) Mirror
(c) Large jar
(d) Scarab & [...][;]over
(e) Gold ring [drawing]
(f) 3 gold earrings.
(g) 2 small Bez. bl. gl.
(h) 7 gilded stucco eyes.
(i) 7 gold leaf pendants
(j) 2 small bronze figurines (v small.)

[drawings]
(k) Eye of green stone
(l) Gold foil beads & clasp.
(m) Bl. gl. beads
(n) 6 carnelian beads.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.72. 73. 74
T.72.
Rect. shaft ridged as 71. Child at 1 m. at east all in middle, head to N. supine.
Chamber on S. Sarcoph. half out of chamber, bricks above it closing cham.
ber. Sandal, & bl. gl. conoid seal [;] over
face, hands & ears.
T.73.
Rect. shaft, chamber to south
(a) Glaze scarab [drawing]
(b) Three vases [drawings]
T.74. Rect. shaft N & S. ridged, ch. to N distrubed, few bl. gl. beads & in shaft a fragt. of pottery.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.76, 77
Rect. shaft, no chambers
[Scarab in tip of shaft] [drawing]
At once came a body [female] in wooden coffin, head N, prone, few bones of child near her head.
(a) Pot [drawing] in S.E. corner of grave
(b) Square [drawing] ornament of bl. gl. on necklace of black beads
(c) Scarab at l. hand [drawing]
77. Rect shaft, body above head to N, supine. No furniture. Supine.
Below plundered body in shaft head to N, disturbed

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.78, 79
78. [plan]
Rect. shaft head N. body in shaft, blind
79. [plan]
Ridged shaft, long chamber to S body in coffin untouched head to N, supine.

Tomb: T.82, 83
[plan]
T.82.
Ridged, chamber broken from 83.
No finds.
T.83. Undisturbed sand in shaft.
[plan]
Seven sealed jars in chamber on east of a wood coffin.
Abandoned by us owing to a dangerous fall of gebel.

Tomb: T.84, 86
T.84.
VI. Dyn square shaft, ch. to S.
girl in coffin on left side, head to north.
T.86.
Rect. shaft [plan]
Ch. to N, fastened up.
Body supine head to N.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.87.
Rect.shaft N.S. near top a child's body disturbed towards N. end.
2 grenn glaze Bez amulets
Bl. gl. frog amulet, 5 beads of glaze (?)
& many white discoid beads of shell.
Slightly lower a pot [drawing] rough ware
Chamber
to N. man's body
head to N. Disturbed.
Long bl. gl. beads [drawing]
& mud fragts with cloth impression on one side & [drawing] on other.

Tomb: T.88.
Disturbed turba burial near top.
Three carnel. beads & 2 wh. gl. (?) beads [drawing]. Bones broken up.
Whitish frog amulet.

Cemetery: South
Tomb: T.91.
Rect. shaft, N & S.
A. Child at corner [plan] in coffin head to E
B. Woman lower head to N, in wooden coffin. On her left side. Beads & bl. gl. stamp at r. hand (up to chin)
scarab at left hand [drawing]
Bl. gl. hedgehog above
Beads bl. gl. & red
Long bead [drawing]
C. Chamber to N. body plundered.

Tomb: T.101.
Turba, head to E, body on rt. side
Below it a VI. Dyn shaft, chamber to W. Full of drift sand.
102. VI Dyn shaft, body on left side[;]103. VI Dyn. shaft, chamber to N. womans body, head to N on right side.
104. Turba, girl's body, head to N. on right side, hands down[;]105. VI Dyn. shaft. body on l. side, pot, sealed, in N corner of chamber
106. Turba, body in wooden sarcoph. head removed, supine, S.E.[;]107. Turba. Body head to N.E., crouched, on rt. side hands up to face.

120. Rect. shaft, chamber S, broken in from the blind shaft to south. Male body on back head to N. No furniture[;]121. Turba grave, old man, 4 teeth left. Supine head S. hands to side. Coffin stucco on wood, painted and shaped to shoulders. Three broken vases on top. Three fragments underneath (not in coffin, probably did not belong)
Roman vault, ran due E + W, one mummy, head to E. One fragt. at gold leaf on breast, under throat. Two Roman handled jars. A roman jug.
